Video and Streaming

At the heart of the camera is a DX-format 20.9MP CMOS sensor, which benefits not only video production needs but also makes the Z30 a highly capable stills camera, too.

UHD 4K recording up to 30p is supported for crisp, high-resolution video needs. Full HD 120p recording is available, too, for slow-motion playback.

For longer takes, streaming, and other instances where you need constant power, the Z30 can be powered via the USB Type-C port.

Photo Capabilities

The large DX-format sensor benefits working in low-light conditions by producing imagery with low noise, high clarity, and a useful sensitivity range from ISO 100-51200, or up to ISO 25600 when recording video.

For photographing fast-moving action, a top continuous shooting speed up to 11 fps is available.

The Coolpix 5700's magnesium alloy body gives it a solid feel, while its nicely curved grip provides a comfortable and steadying handhold. Weighing a moderate 1.2 pounds with batteries and media installed, the Coolpix 5700 has a relatively compact design for a camera of its class. If you prefer to use the EVF instead of the swivel LCD, you can adjust its focus with the little diopter dial next to the eyepiece. 

One of the prominent features of the Coolpix 5700 is its 8X zoom lens, which provides a hefty zoom range of 35mm to 205mm (35mm camera equivalent). Relatively fast with a maximum aperture of 2.8, the lens stops down to only f/8.0. The lens is the first one on a Coolpix model to employ extra-low-dispersion glass elements for improved photo quality and sharpness. The Coolpix 5700's full battery of exposure, metering, white-balance, and autofocus modes is complemented by tools such as in-camera image sharpening, contrast, saturation, and noise reduction controls.

Overall, the Coolpix 5700 delivered excellent image quality, with plenty of resolution and excellent color throughout my testing. Colors were natural and accurate, with appropriate saturation levels. Nikon got the color management on the Coolpix 5700 just right. In the areas of its greatest strength, its macro and low light capabilities are really outstanding.
